                    The Department of State to the
                            British Embassy</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d209</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">209</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-11T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="209" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d209">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860f.4016/6–2845</note>
                <head>No. 209 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">British Embassy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="1" xml:id="d209fn1">For the full text
                            of this memorandum, see <ref target="#d440">document No. 440</ref>. This
                            paper was a reply to <ref target="#d173">document No. 173</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <p>The Department of State believes that an exchange of views on the whole question
                    of the transfers of ethnic minority groups in Europe is not required at this
                    time in view of the clear statements of policy by the British and American
                    Governments, and could be deferred pending a possible discussion of this
                    question at the forthcoming tripartite conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, [<date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-11">July 11,
                            1945</date>.]</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
